The paper discusses a new predictive test selection strategy that uses machine learning techniques to select a subset of tests to exercise for each change submitted to the continuous integration system. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with improving the testing process. The use of machine learning also suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions a monolithic repository, which suggests a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). Finally, the use of machine learning for predictive test selection suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
